The paper deals with explaining and debugging neural network-based object detectors, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach presented in the paper involves a probabilistic programming language, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance assessment and rule extraction, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE).
